On December 13, 2016, the President signed into law H.R. 34, also known as the "21st Century Cures Act." This act aims to modify current medical research and drug development processes, reauthorize the National Institutes of Health, fund State efforts to prevent and treat opioid abuse, make changes to health and justice authorities regarding mental health and substance use disorders, and make updates to Medicare, Medicaid, and health information technology.